{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019TyEVD6WtZvsp84jtHuEjJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem is clear: the `discovery.seed_hosts` in the ConfigMap points to:\n- `es-cluster-0.es-cluster.default.svc.cluster.local`\n- `es-cluster-1.es-cluster.default.svc.cluster.local`\n- `es-cluster-2.es-cluster.default.svc.cluster.local`\n\nBut the actual namespace is `elasticsearch`, not `default`. So it should be:\n- `es-cluster-0.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n- `es-cluster-1.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n- `es-cluster-2.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n\nThe `node.name` is empty in the ConfigMap but relies on the `${POD_NAME}` environment variable set in the StatefulSet spec. To fix this, I need to patch the ConfigMap with the correct namespace in the seed hosts, then delete the es-cluster-2 pod so it can rejoin with the updated configuration.\n\nI should also check how the StatefulSet mounts the ConfigMap and whether there are any other configuration issues to address.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":718,"cache_read_input_tokens":33321,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":718},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a6963432-1de4-4859-853a-02785121faaa","uuid":"5ffebb4f-03c7-49eb-bbd3-342cc1cef804","request_id":"req_011CcRF68fSa2uz7aQkBLwkp"}
