{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016f7AtETKmcP34iqqVQjdPn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three verification criteria are met:\n\n1. **Cluster health is green** — `status: green`, 4/4 active shards, 0 unassigned.\n2. **All 3 nodes appear in `/_cat/nodes`** — es-cluster-0 (master), es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2 all present.\n3. **`app-data` index is readable** — count returns 1 document successfully.\n\n**What was broken and how it was fixed:**\n\nThe precondition injected a fault by patching the `es-config` ConfigMap so that `discovery.seed_hosts` referenced the wrong namespace (`default`) instead of the actual namespace (`elasticsearch`). The correct DNS hostnames for the headless service are:\n- `es-cluster-N.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n\nWhen es-cluster-2 was restarted (after its PVC was deleted), it couldn't find any seed hosts to bootstrap discovery, so it couldn't rejoin the two-node cluster that was already running.\n\nThe fix patched the ConfigMap to use the correct `elasticsearch` namespace in all three seed host entries, then deleted es-cluster-2 so the StatefulSet controller recreated it with the corrected config. On restart, it successfully discovered the existing nodes and rejoined the cluster."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":220,"cache_read_input_tokens":36286,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":220},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a6963432-1de4-4859-853a-02785121faaa","uuid":"e1b7ed59-ecb6-4055-8173-66cdd7bd96fe","request_id":"req_011CcRFD5CXXVzh4yUdGfcWn"}
